        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 9:45PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 944 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Granger Butte, or 28 miles northeast of Weiser, moving northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Granger Butte around 950 PM MDT.
Indian Mountain around 1010 PM MDT.
Tamarack Ski Area and northern Cascade Reservoir around 1020 PM
MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
